  "ai": {
    "summary": "Illustrates the process of merging a base model with a LoRA adaptor into a single model directory, ready for deployment with inference frameworks like vLLM",
    "whatItShows": "This flowchart illustrates the transformation of a fine-tuned model from a 'base model + LoRA adaptor' combination into a single, merged model directory. It highlights the use of PEFT's merge_and_unload() function to consolidate the adaptor weights into the base model, making it directly loadable by standard inference frameworks like vLLM.",
    "whenToUse": "Use this process when preparing a LoRA-fine-tuned model for production deployment to simplify the inference serving architecture and reduce overhead associated with managing separate base and adaptor weights. It's crucial before deploying to inference engines that expect a single model artifact.",
    "howToAdapt": "This pattern can be adapted for any PEFT method that involves an adaptor, not just LoRA. The specific merge_and_unload() function might vary by library, but the principle of consolidating weights remains. It can also be extended to include further optimization steps like quantization or compilation before final deployment.",
    "keyConcepts": ["LoRA", "PEFT", "Model Merging", "vLLM", "Model Deployment"],
    "fallback": false
  },
